{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"79c6f478-f82e-4aa9-80b6-35fa554f41ee","content":"Yes, you'll hit compatibility issues. **MSTest v3 dropped support for two of your three target frameworks:**\n\n| TFM | MSTest v3 Support |\n|---|---|\n| `net462` | ✅ Supported |\n| `netcoreapp3.1` | ❌ Dropped |\n| `net5.0` | ❌ Dropped |\n\nMSTest v3 requires **.NET 6.0+** for .NET (Core) targets. Both `netcoreapp3.1` and `net5.0` are end-of-life and no longer supported.\n\n**To migrate**, you'd need to update your TFMs — for example, replacing `net5.0` → `net6.0` (or `net8.0`) and `netcoreapp3.1` → `net6.0`. If you must continue testing on those older runtimes, you'll need to stay on MSTest v2.\n\nWould you like me to update the project for MSTest v3 with modern TFMs?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"dd82aaea-f17b-4d72-abe1-0b25b3593e78","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user has a test project that multi-targets `net5.0`, `net462`, and `netcoreapp3.1`. They want to migrate from MSTest v2 (2.2.10) to MSTest v3.\n\nLet me check the MSTest v3 compatibility. MSTest v3 dropped support for several older TFMs. Specifically:\n- MSTest v3 requires at minimum .NET 6.0 for .NET (Core) targets, and .NET Framework 4.6.2 is still supported.\n- Actually, let me think more carefully. MSTest v3 supports:\n  - .NET Framework 4.6.2+\n  - .NET 6.0+\n\nSo `net462` will work fine, but `net5.0` and `netcoreapp3.1` won't be compatible with MSTest v3 since they're below the minimum .NET 6.0 requirement for Core targets. The user will need to either drop those target frameworks or stick with MSTest v2.","outputTokens":509,"requestId":"0428:13FE50:162FD9A:17A2EE5:6A033805"},"id":"b0ae8717-2224-4df1-a7f8-7f8ba0c27d22","timestamp":"2026-05-12T14:24:21.412Z","parentId":"b9f8dc56-56b7-4af8-bd43-4014192db6b2"}
